&gt; Does anybody know how to load and unload cantera related &quot;stuff&quot;
&gt; within subfunctions of big MATLAB codes in a definte way?

MATLAB has a number of limitations as a front end for Cantera, or any  
C++ code.  The biggest problem is that it does not provide a good way  
to manage memory allocation for cases where the MATLAB code calls C  
or C++ code that allocates some memory.  MATLAB does not provide  
&quot;destructors&quot; for classes, so when an object created by a call to  
&quot;GRI30&quot;, for example, is deleted, only the MATLAB variables are  
released, not any memory allocated by Cantera.
This is a fundamental limitation of the object model used in MATLAB,  
unlike the much more robust object model of Python.

I always get a bit nervous when I hear people describing &quot;big&quot;  
calculations done using Cantera and MATLAB.  My recommendation would  
be to switch to Python, or even go all the way to C++...
