&gt; p.s.: just a tip:
&gt; I&#39;ve recognized a &quot;pointer like&quot; behaviour of solution variables in
&gt; MATLAB.
&gt; if you do something like:
&gt; g1=GRI30;
&gt; g2=g1;
&gt; set(g1,&#39;T&#39;,400);
&gt; The set command will have effect on BOTH variables g1 and g2!!!!
&gt;
The MATLAB objects just store pointers to the underlying C++ objects;  
the statement &quot;g2=g1&quot; copies the pointer. If you want a new,  
independent object, you have to call a constructor. So you would need  
to write:
g1=GRI30;
g2=GRI30;
instead of assigning g1 to g2.

